\pard\intbl\ql
{{\b
Aims of the course: }}\cell\row\pard
}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
\clvertalt\cellx9430
\pard\intbl\ql
{The objective of the course is to introduce students to the topic 
of a general management applicable for every type of organisation 
\_ profit and non profit, SME's, big and multinational\'2e Successful 
management requires knowlwedge of basic managerial functions and key 
managerial approaches and techniques\'2e  }\cell\row\pard
}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
\clvertalt\cellx9430
\pard\intbl\ql
{\~}\cell\row\pard
}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
\clvertalt\cellx9430
\pard\intbl\ql
{{\b
Learning outcomes and competences: }}\cell\row\pard
}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
\clvertalt\cellx9430
\pard\intbl\ql
{Upon successful completion of this course, students will be able to 
explain present\_day approaches in management, they will be able to 
understand differences between various managerial functions and master 
another know\_how connected with management:\line
\_ identify and recognize current and possible future trends in development 
of management science\line
\_ define major roles of managers of different levels in organisations\line
\_ critically evaluate ethical problems and solve them\line
\_ construct organisational structures for concrete organisations\line
\_ use different managerial tools and methods\line
\_ recognise different managerial styles and approaches\line
\line
Specifically:\line
\line
They will understand the role of managers in organisations and importance 
of management for organisations\'2e They will be able to articulate 
and use planning categories\'2e They will learn to choose proper methods 
and tools that will help them to decide and will be able to suggest 
proper organisational structure depending on concrete situation of 
organisation\'2e They will be able to identify adequate tools of motivation 
and execute controlling processes in proper way\'2e In addition they 
will be able to choose and apply proper style of leadership and motivation, 
decide on right style of management\'2e Great attention is paid to 
their ability to identify and estimate ethical problems and dilemmas 
and to solve them\'2e The course is finished with excursion to the 
history of management that allows students to synthetise the knowledge 
of the course\'2e \line
\line
Overall learning outcomes:\line
}\cell\row\pard
}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
\clvertalt\cellx9430
\pard\intbl\ql
{\~}\cell\row\pard
